"If you need to manually configure a Salt client to connect to the "
"{productname} Server, edit the Salt client configuration file with the "
"correct network details.  For more information about Salt minion "
"configuration file contact method, see "
"xref:client-configuration:registration-cli.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-salt.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Onboarding Details"
msgstr "Detalls de l'Onboarding"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-salt.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Salt has its own database to keep the keys for the minions. This needs to be "
"kept in sync with the {productname} database.  As soon as the key is "
"accepted in Salt, the onboarding process in {productname} starts.  The "
"onboarding process will look for existing systems in the {productname} "
"database by searching for the ``minion_id`` and the ``machine-id``.  If "
"nothing is found, the new system gets created.  In case an entry with the "
"``minion_id`` or the ``machine-id`` is found, that system will be migrated "
"to match the new system.  In case there is a match for both entries, and "
"they are not the same system, the onboarding will be aborted with an error.  "
"In this case the administrator needs to resolve the conflict by removing at "
"least on of the systems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Salt Bundle"
msgstr "Salt Bundle"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is Salt Bundle?"
msgstr "Què és Salt Bundle?"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:3
msgid ""
"The Salt Bundle is a single binary package containing Salt Minion, Python 3, "
"required Python modules, and libraries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The Salt Bundle is shipped with Python 3 and all the requirements for Salt "
"to run. Thus Salt Bundle does not use the Python version install on the "
"client as system software.  The Salt Bundle can be installed on clients that "
"do not meet the requirements for a given Salt version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:5
msgid ""
"It is also possible to use the Salt Bundle on systems that run a Salt Minion "
"connected to a Salt Master other than the {productname} Salt Master."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client Registration with Salt Bundle as a Minion"
msgstr "Registre del client amb Salt Bundle com a Minion"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:7
msgid ""
"The registration method with the Salt Bundle is the recommended registration "
"method.  This section explains the advantages and limitations of the current "
"implementation.  The Salt Bundle is provided as the "
"[package]``venv-salt-minion`` that consists of Salt, Python 3, and the "
"Python modules Salt depends on.  Bootstrapping with {webui} is using Salt "
"Bundle as well, so bootstrapping with {webui} is not Python dependant.  "
"Using the Salt Bundle, it is no longer needed that the client provides any "
"Python interpreter or modules."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:8
msgid ""
"If you bootstrap new clients, registration with the Salt Bundle is the "
"default method.  You can switch existing clients to the Salt Bundle method.  "
"If you switch, the [package]``salt-minion`` package and its dependencies "
"will stay installed."
msgstr ""
"Si arrenqueu clients nous, registrar-vos amb el Salt Bundle és el mètode per "
"defecte.  Podeu canviar els clients existents al mètode Salt Bundle.  Si "
"canvieu, el paquet [package].salt-minion. i les seves dependències romandran "
"instal·lades."

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using the Salt Bundle with the Salt Minion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:10
msgid ""
"The Salt Bundle can be used with the Salt Minion managed by the Salt Master "
"other than {productname} Server at the same time.  If the Salt Bundle is "
"installed on a client {productname} Server will manage the configuration "
"files of the Salt Bundle, the configuration files of "
"[literal]``salt-minion`` will not be managed in this case.  For more "
"information, see "
"xref:client-configuration:registration-cli.adoc#_salt_bundle_configuration[Salt "
"Bundle configuration]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:11
msgid ""
"To bootstrap a client with the Salt Minion managed by the Salt Master other "
"than {productname} Server it is recommended to use "
"[command]``mgr-bootstrap`` [option]``--force-bundle`` when generating the "
"bootstrap script, or to set [option]``FORCE_VENV_SALT_MINION`` to `1` in the "
"bootstrap script.  For bootstrapping with {webui} "
"[literal]``mgr_force_venv_salt_minion`` set to [literal]``true`` pillar can "
"be specified globally.  For more information, see "
"xref:specialized-guides:salt/salt-states-and-pillars.adoc[Salt States and "
"Pillars]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Switching from Salt Minion to Salt Bundle"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:13
msgid ""
"The Salt state [literal]``util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion`` is available to "
"switch from [package]``salt-minion`` to [package]``venv-salt-minion``.  It "
"is recommended to switch to [package]``venv-salt-minion`` in two steps to "
"avoid trouble with shifting processes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Procedure: Switching with [literal]``util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion`` state "
"to [package]``venv-salt-minion``"
msgstr ""
"Procediment: Canvi amb [literal] toutil.mgrswitchtovenvminion to estat a "
"[package] tovenv-salt-minion to"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Apply [literal]``util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion`` with no pillar specified "
"first.  This will result in the switch to [package]``venv-salt-minion`` with "
"copying configuration files etc.  It will not clean up the original "
"[package]``salt-minion`` configurations and its packages."
msgstr ""
"Aplica [literal].util.mgrswitchtovenvminion. sense cap pilar especificat "
"primer.  Això resultarà en el canvi a [package].venv-salt-minion. amb la "
"còpia de fitxers de configuració, etc. No netejarà les configuracions "
"originals [package].salt-minion. i els seus paquets."

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt <minion_id> state.apply util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion\n"
msgstr "sal <minionid> estat.apply util.mgrswitchtovenvminion\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Apply [literal]``util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion`` with "
"[literal]``mgr_purge_non_venv_salt`` set to [literal]``True`` to remove "
"[package]``salt-minion`` and with [literal]``mgr_purge_non_venv_salt_files`` "
"set to [literal]``True`` to remove all the files related to "
"[package]``salt-minion``.  This second step ensures the first step was "
"processed, and then removes the old configuration files and the now obsolete "
"[package]``salt-minion`` package."
msgstr ""
"Aplica [literal].util.mgrswitchtovenvminion. amb [literal]."
"mgrpurgenonvenvsalt. establert a [literal].True to per eliminar [package] "
"tosalt-minion to i amb [literal].mgrpurgenonvenvsaltfiles. establert a "
"[literal].True. per eliminar tots els fitxers relacionats amb [package].salt-"
"minion..  Aquest segon pas assegura que el primer pas s'ha processat, i "
"després elimina els fitxers de configuració antics i el paquet [package"
"].salt-minion. ara obsolet."

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"salt <minion_id> state.apply util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion "
"pillar='{\"mgr_purge_non_venv_salt_files\": True, "
"\"mgr_purge_non_venv_salt\": True}'\n"
msgstr ""
"sal <minionid> estat.aplica util.mgrswitchtovenvminion pilar\":'{"
"\"mgrpurgenonvenvsaltfiles\": Cert, \"mgrpurgenonvenvsalt\": Cert}'\n"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:19
msgid ""
"In case of running the second step of switching with skipping the first "
"step, state apply process could fail as it requires stopping the "
"[systemitem]``salt-minion`` which is used to execute the command on the "
"client side."
msgstr ""
"En cas d'executar el segon pas de commutar amb saltar el primer pas, el "
"procés d'aplicació d'estat podria fallar, ja que requereix aturar el "
"[systemitem]altsalt-minion. que s'utilitza per executar l'ordre al costat "
"del client."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:20
msgid ""
"On the other hand, it is also possible to avoid installing the Salt Bundle "
"and keep using [package]``salt-minion`` instead.  In this case, specify one "
"of these options:"
msgstr ""
"D'altra banda, també és possible evitar instal·lar el Salt Bundle i seguir "
"utilitzant [package].salt-minion. en el seu lloc.  En aquest cas, "
"especifiqueu una d'aquestes opcions:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:21
msgid "Execute [command]``mgr-bootstrap`` with [option]``--no-bundle`` option."
msgstr "Executa [command].mgr-bootstrap with amb l'opció [option].--no-bundle.."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:22
msgid ""
"Set [literal]``AVOID_VENV_SALT_MINION`` to [literal]``1`` in the generated "
"bootstrap script."
msgstr ""
"Estableix [literal].AVOIDVENVSALTMINION to a [literal]11. a l'script "
"d'arrencada generat."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:23
msgid ""
"For bootstrap state set the [literal]``mgr_avoid_venv_salt_minion`` pillar "
"to [literal]``True``."
msgstr ""
"Per a l'estat de bootstrap establiu el pilar [literal]."
"mgravoidvenvsaltminion. a [literal].True.."

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Salt SSH with the Salt Bundle"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:25
msgid "The Salt Bundle is also used when performing Salt SSH actions to clients."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:26
msgid ""
"A shell script deploys the Salt Bundle onto the target system without "
"installing [package]``venv-salt-minion`` before any Salt command is "
"executed. Since the Salt Bundle contains the whole Salt code base, no "
"[literal]``salt-thin`` is deployed. Salt SSH (including bootstrapping using "
"the {webui}) uses the Python 3 interpreter within the bundle. The target "
"system does not need to have any other Python interpreter installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:27
msgid ""
"The Python 3 deployed with the Bundle is used to handle Salt SSH session on "
"the client, so Salt SSH (including bootstrapping with {webui}) is not "
"dependant on Python installed on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:28
msgid ""
"The bootstrap repository must be created before bootstrapping the client "
"with {webui}. Salt SSH is using the Salt Bundle taken from the bootstrap "
"repository based on the detected target operating system.  For more "
"information, see "
"xref:client-configuration:bootstrap-repository.adoc#_prepare_to_create_a_bootstrap_repository[Prepare "
"to Create a Bootstrap Repository]"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:29
msgid ""
"Using `salt-thin` can be enabled as a fallback method, but it requires "
"Python 3 to be installed on the client.  This method is not recommended nor "
"supported and exists for development purposes only.  Set "
"[option]``web.ssh_use_salt_thin`` to `true` in the "
"[path]``/etc/rhn/rhn.conf`` configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Push via Salt SSH"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Push via Salt SSH is used in environments where Salt clients cannot reach "
"the {productname} Server directly.  In this environment, clients are located "
"in a firewall-protected zone called a DMZ.  No system within the DMZ is "
"authorized to open a connection to the internal network, including the "
"{productname} Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:3
msgid ""
"The Push via Salt SSH method creates an encrypted tunnel from the "
"{productname} Server on the internal network to the clients located on the "
"DMZ.  After all actions and events are executed, the tunnel is closed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The server uses the Salt SSH to contact the clients at regular intervals, "
"checking in and performing scheduled actions and events.  For more "
"information about Salt SSH, see "
"xref:specialized-guides:salt/salt-ssh.adoc[Salt SSH]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:5
msgid ""
"This contact method works for Salt clients only.  For traditional clients, "
"use Push via SSH."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:6
msgid ""
"This image demonstrates the Push via Salt SSH process path.  All items left "
"of the [systemitem]``Taskomatic`` block represent processes running on the "
"{productname} client."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt-ssh-contact-taigon.png"
msgstr "salt-ssh-contact-taigon.png"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:8
msgid ""
"To use Push via Salt SSH, you must have the SSH daemon running on the "
"client, and reachable by the [systemitem]``salt-api`` daemon running on the "
"{productname} Server.  Additionally, Python must be available on the remote "
"system, and be a version supported by Salt."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:9
msgid ""
"{rhel}{nbsp}5, {centos}{nbsp}5, and earlier are not supported, as they use "
"unsupported versions of Python."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Registering Clients with Push via Salt SSH"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:11
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[Bootstrapping] and "
"complete the appropriate fields."
msgstr ""
"A {productname} {webui}, navegueu al menú:Systems[Bootstrapping] i completeu "
"els camps apropiats."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:12
msgid "Select an activation key with the Push via SSH contact method configured."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:13
msgid ""
"For more information about activation keys, see "
"xref:client-configuration:activation-keys.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:14
msgid "Check the [systemitem]``Manage system completely via SSH`` checkbox."
msgstr ""
"Marqueu la casella [systemitem].Gestioneu el sistema completament mitjançant "
"SSH.."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:16
msgid ""
"Confirm that the system has been registered correctly by navigating to "
"menu:Systems[Overview]."
msgstr ""
"Confirmeu que el sistema s'ha registrat correctament navegant al "
"menú:Systems[Overview]."

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "Available Parameters"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:18
msgid ""
"When you are configuring Push via Salt SSH, you can modify parameters that "
"are used when a system is registered, including the host, activation key, "
"and password.  The password is used only for bootstrapping, it is not saved "
"anywhere.  All future SSH sessions are authorized via a key/certificate "
"pair.  These parameters are configured in menu:Systems[Bootstrapping]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:19
msgid ""
"You can also configure persistent parameters that are are used system-wide, "
"including the sudo user.  For more information on configuring the sudo user, "
"see xref:client-configuration:contact-methods-pushssh.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Action Execution"
msgstr "Execució d'acció"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:21
msgid ""
"The Push via Salt SSH feature uses taskomatic to execute scheduled actions "
"using [command]``salt-ssh``.  The taskomatic job periodically checks for "
"scheduled actions and executes them.  Unlike Push via SSH on traditional "
"clients, the Push via Salt SSH feature executes a complete "
"[command]``salt-ssh`` call based on the scheduled action."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:22
msgid ""
"By default, twenty Salt SSH actions can be executed at a time.  You can "
"increase the number of actions that can be executed in parallel, by adding "
"these lines to your configuration file, and adjusting the value of "
"``parallel_threads`` upwards.  We recommend you keep the number of parallel "
"actions low, to avoid problems:"
msgstr ""
"Per defecte, es poden executar vint accions Salt SSH alhora.  Podeu "
"augmentar el nombre d'accions que es poden executar en paral·lel, afegint "
"aquestes línies al fitxer de configuració i ajustant el valor de ."
"parallelthreads. cap amunt.  Us recomanem mantenir baix el nombre d'accions "
"paral·leles, per evitar problemes:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"taskomatic.com.redhat.rhn.taskomatic.task.SSHMinionActionExecutor.parallel_threads "
"= <number>\n"
"org.quartz.threadPool.threadCount = <value of parallel_threads + 20>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:24
msgid ""
"This adjusts the number of actions that can run in parallel on any one "
"client and the total number of worker threads used by taskomatic.  If "
"actions needs to be run on multiple clients, actions are always executed "
"sequentially on each client."
msgstr ""
"Això ajusta el nombre d'accions que poden executar-se en paral·lel en "
"qualsevol client i el nombre total de fils de treball utilitzats per "
"taskomatic.  Si les accions s'han d'executar en múltiples clients, les "
"accions sempre s'executen seqüencialment en cada client."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:25
msgid ""
"If the clients are connected through a proxy, you need to adjust the "
"``MaxSessions`` settings on the proxy.  In this case, set the number of "
"parallel connections to be three times the total number of clients."
msgstr ""
"Si els clients estan connectats a través d'un servidor intermediari, heu "
"d'ajustar la configuració de .MaxSessions. al servidor intermediari.  En "
"aquest cas, establir el nombre de connexions paral·leles a tres vegades el "
"nombre total de clients."

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Future Features"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:27
msgid ""
"There are some features that are not yet supported on Push via Salt SSH.  "
"These features do not work on Salt SSH clients:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:28
msgid "OpenSCAP auditing"
msgstr "Auditoria OpenSCAP"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:29
msgid "Beacons, resulting in:"
msgstr "Beacons, resultant en:"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:30
msgid ""
"Installing a package on a system using [command]``zypper`` does not invoke "
"the package refresh."
msgstr ""
"Instal·lar un paquet en un sistema utilitzant [command].zypper. no invoca "
"l'actualització del paquet."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:31
msgid ""
"Virtual Host functions (for example, a host to guests) does not work if the "
"virtual host system is Salt SSH-based."
msgstr ""
"Les funcions d'amfitrió virtual (per exemple, un amfitrió per a convidats) "
"no funcionen si el sistema d'amfitrió virtual està basat en Salt SSH."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:32
msgid ""
"For more information about Salt SSH, see "
"https://docs.saltstack.com/en/latest/topics/ssh/."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-traditional.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Contact Methods for Traditional Clients"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-traditional.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Traditional clients can communicate with the {productname} Server using a "
"range of methods."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-traditional.adoc:3
msgid ""
"The {productname} daemon ([command]``rhnsd``) runs on traditional client "
"systems and periodically connects with {productname} to check for new "
"updates and notifications."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-traditional.adoc:4
msgid ""
"Push via SSH is used in environments where clients cannot reach the "
"{productname} Server directly.  In this environment, clients are located in "
"a firewall-protected zone called a DMZ.  No system within the DMZ is "
"authorized to open a connection to the internal network, including the "
"{productname} Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-traditional.adoc:5
msgid ""
"OSAD is an alternative contact method between {productname} and traditional "
"clients.  OSAD allows traditional clients to execute scheduled actions "
"immediately."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-traditional.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Traditional clients will be deprecated with the next {productname} version "
"and will not be supported with future releases.  Be aware that when "
"migrating from traditional clients to Salt minions you do not have to delete "
"the registered clients before. You can just register them as Salt minions "
"and Salt will do the necessary steps with the traditional client. If you "
"already deleted the traditional client and the registration as Salt minion "
"is not possible anymore, see "
"xref:installation-and-upgrade:troubleshooting.adoc[Troubleshooting]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Custom System Information"
msgstr "Informació personalitzada del sistema"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:2
msgid ""
"You can include customized system information about your clients.  System "
"information is defined as key:value pairs, which can be assigned to "
"clients.  For example, you can define a key:value pair for a particular "
"processor, then assign that key to all clients that have that processor "
"installed.  Custom system information is categorized, and can be searched "
"using the {productname} {webui}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:3
msgid ""
"Before you begin, you need to create a key that allows you to store custom "
"information."
msgstr ""
"Abans de començar, heu de crear una clau que us permeti emmagatzemar "
"informació personalitzada."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Creating a Custom System Information Key"
msgstr "Procediment: Creació d'una clau d'informació personalitzada del sistema"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:5
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[Custom System Info], "
"and click btn:[Create Key]."
msgstr ""
"A la {productname} {webui}, navegueu al menú:Systems[Informació del sistema "
"personalitzat], i feu clic a btn:[Crea clau]."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:6
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Key Label`` field, add a name for your key.  Do not use "
"spaces.  For example, ``intel-x86_64-quadcore``."
msgstr ""
"Al camp [guimenu].Etiqueta de la clau., afegiu un nom per a la vostra clau.  "
"No facis servir espais.  Per exemple, .intel-x8664-quadcore.."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:7
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Description`` field, provide any additional information "
"required."
msgstr ""
"Al camp [guimenu].Descripció., proporcioneu qualsevol informació addicional "
"requerida."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:8
msgid "Repeat for each key you require."
msgstr "Repeteix per a cada clau que necessitis."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:9
msgid ""
"For traditional clients, this information is stored in the {productname} "
"database.  For Salt clients, this information is stored in a Salt pillar.  "
"You can retrieve this information from a Salt client with a command such as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt $minionid pillar.get custom_info:key1\n"
msgstr "sal $minionid pilar.get custominfo:key1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:11
msgid "This command will result in an output such as:"
msgstr "Aquesta ordre resultarà en una sortida com:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$minionid:\n"
"    val1\n"
msgstr ""
"$minionid:\n"
"    val1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:13
msgid ""
"When you have created some custom system information keys, you can apply "
"them to clients."
msgstr ""
"Quan hàgiu creat algunes claus personalitzades d'informació del sistema, les "
"podeu aplicar als clients."

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Applying Custom Information Keys to Clients"
msgstr ""
"Procediment: Aplicació de claus d'informació personalitzades als clients"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:15
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to [guimenu]``Systems``, click the "
"client to apply custom information to, and navigate to the "
"menu:Details[Custom Info] tab."
msgstr ""
"A la {productname} {webui}, navegueu a [guimenu].Sistemes., feu clic al "
"client per aplicar informació personalitzada i navegueu a la pestanya "
"menú:Detalls[Informació personalitzada]."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:16
msgid "Click btn:[Create Value]."
msgstr "Feu clic a btn:[Crea valor]."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:17
msgid "Locate the value you want to apply, and click the key label."
msgstr ""
"Localitzeu el valor que voleu aplicar i feu clic a l'etiqueta de la clau."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:18
msgid "In the [guimenu]``Value`` field, provide any additional information."
msgstr "Al camp [guimenu].Valor., proporcioneu qualsevol informació addicional."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:19
msgid "Click btn:[Update Key] to apply the custom information to the client."
msgstr ""
"Feu clic a btn:[Update Key] per aplicar la informació personalitzada al "
"client."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/custom-info.adoc:20
msgid ""
"For more information about configuration management, see "
"xref:client-configuration:configuration-management.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"Per obtenir més informació sobre la gestió de la configuració, vegeu xref"
":client-configuration:configuration-management.adoc[]."

#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client Deletion"
msgstr "Supressió del client"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:2
msgid ""
"If you need to remove a client from your {productname} Server, you can use "
"the {webui} to delete it.  This procedure works for both traditional and "
"Salt clients."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Deleting a Client"
msgstr "Procediment: Suprimir un client"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:4
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[System List] and "
"select the client to delete."
msgstr ""
"A {productname} {webui}, navegueu al menú:Systems[Llista de sistemes] i "
"seleccioneu el client a suprimir."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:5
msgid "Click btn:[Delete System]."
msgstr "Feu clic a btn:[Suprimeix el sistema]."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:6
msgid "Check the details and click btn:[Delete Profile] to confirm."
msgstr ""
"Comproveu els detalls i feu clic a btn:[Suprimeix el perfil] per a confirmar-"
"ho."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:7
msgid ""
"For Salt clients, {productname} attempts to clean up additional "
"configuration.  If the client cannot be contacted, you are given the option "
"to cancel the deletion, or delete the client without cleaning up the "
"configuration files."
msgstr ""
"Per als clients de Salt, {productname} intenta netejar la configuració "
"addicional.  Si no es pot contactar amb el client, se li dona l'opció de "
"cancel·lar la supressió, o eliminar el client sense netejar els fitxers de "
"configuració."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:8
msgid ""
"You can also delete multiple clients using the system set manager.  For more "
"information about the system set manager, see "
"xref:client-configuration:system-set-manager.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:9
msgid ""
"It is not possible to automatically clean up a a traditional client after "
"deleting it. You have to take care of this yourself. Furthermore cleaning up "
"a Salt minion does not remove Salt itself."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/delete-clients.adoc:10
msgid ""
"Normally you migrate a traditional client to a Salt minion without deleting "
"the client. Salt automatically detects that you have a traditional client "
"and does the necessary changes itself. But if you already deleted the "
"traditional client and want to register it as a Salt minion again, see "
"xref:installation-and-upgrade:troubleshooting.adoc[Troubleshooting]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/gpg-keys.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "GPG Keys"
msgstr "Tecles GPG"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/gpg-keys.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Clients use GPG keys to check the authenticity of software packages before "
"they are installed.  Only trusted software can be installed on clients."
msgstr ""
"Els clients utilitzen claus GPG per comprovar l'autenticitat dels paquets de "
"programari abans que s'instal·lin.  Només es pot instal·lar programari de "
"confiança als clients."

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/gpg-keys.adoc:3
msgid ""
"In most cases, you do not need to adjust the GPG settings to be able to "
"install software on your clients."
msgstr ""
"En la majoria dels casos, no cal que ajusteu la configuració de GPG per a "
"poder instal·lar programari als vostres clients."

